<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,640,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,320,1274,1300]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species can be easily recognized by the piceous base of the clavus and appendix of the forewing, the triangular subgenital plates, the more acutely pointed apophysis of the style, the apex of the aedeagal shaft and the presence of a small lobe on the caudal margin of the male pygofer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,1140,1386,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,640,1412]" box="[197,1140,1386,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,338,1386,1412]" pageId="3" pageNumber="18">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named for the small ventral lobe of the male pygofer.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
